# ─── FairArena Client — Environment Variables ────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in values for your deployment.
# All VITE_* vars are embedded at build time (Vite replaces them).
#
# ─── Vercel (frontend) + VPS (backend) split deployment ──────────────────────
#
# Set this to your VPS backend URL when deploying the frontend on Vercel
# (or any static host) and the backend on a separate server.
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
#   VITE_API_URL=https://vps.yourdomain.com:4000
#
# Leave EMPTY (or omit the file entirely) for local development —
# the Vite dev server proxy will forward /api/* and /terminal to localhost:4000.
VITE_API_URL=

# ─── Notes ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# • WebSocket URL is derived automatically from VITE_API_URL:
#     https://... → wss://...
#     http://...  → ws://...
# • Make sure your VPS backend has CORS configured to allow your Vercel domain.
#   Set ALLOWED_ORIGINS in the server .env (see root .env.example).
